to fix (I added an issue to at least cover your list below).

St.Ack


Eric wrote:
&gt; In regards to running kickUpdate, I&#39;m noticing that many of the
&gt; options for FetchHTTP: the local IP to bind to, the cookie stuff,
&gt; sotimeout-ms, and trust level, you can&#39;t really update mid-crawl
&gt; because they&#39;re only set from FetchHTTP.configureHttp() which is only
&gt; called from FetchHTTP.initialTasks() which is only called (indirectly)
&gt; from CrawlController.requestCrawlStart().  To change these options
&gt; you&#39;d really have to checkpoint and recover the crawl...there is no
&gt; kickUpdate interface for the fetch modules.  Is this a shortcoming, or
&gt; is this documented somewhere?
&gt;
&gt; thanks,
&gt; eric
&gt;
&gt; On Tue, Sep 12, 2006 at 10:34:36AM -0700, Michael Stack wrote:
&gt;   
&gt;&gt; Eric wrote:
&gt;&gt;     
&gt;&gt;&gt; Ah, I was confusing the exception i was getting trying to set an
&gt;&gt;&gt; attribute to a value w/ a comma in it...as far as i can tell there&#39;s
&gt;&gt;&gt; no way to escape a comma in the attribute value in cmdline-jmxclient.
&gt;&gt;&gt;   
&gt;&gt;&gt;       
&gt;&gt; I don&#39;t think it possible since comma is param delimiter.  Suggestions 
&gt;&gt; for how to escape?
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;     
&gt;&gt;&gt; Also, any idea why changing the configuration takes a long time from
&gt;&gt;&gt; the UI but when I change something via JMX it&#39;s instantaneous?  Does
&gt;&gt;&gt; this imply &quot;re-read seeds on config&quot; doesn&#39;t happen when setting from
&gt;&gt;&gt; JMX?
&gt;&gt;&gt;   
&gt;&gt;&gt;       
&gt;&gt; That seems like a promising explanation.  We have to work better on the 
&gt;&gt; separation of UI handling code from internal logic.  I just noticed that 
&gt;&gt; if job is running, a kickUpdate is sent if any edit to UI.  I&#39;ve made an 
&gt;&gt; issue to refactor so this logic is run whether UI or JMX edit.
&gt;&gt;     
&gt;&gt;&gt; Any predictions on the 1.10 release date?  :)
&gt;&gt;&gt;   
&gt;&gt;&gt;       
&gt;&gt; Can you predict whats passed? (smile).
&gt;&gt; St.Ack
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;     
&gt;&gt;&gt; thanks,
&gt;&gt;&gt; eric
