&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; As is, there are limits.  You can&#39;t add/remove modules (e.g. decide 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; rules) nor add overrides via JMX but we intend to fix this in the 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; release after the pending one.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; You can add a new job based on a jar that includes an order and seeds 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; (and possibly overrides).  You could do desired macro edits on an 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; order.xml template and then post the bundle to a remote crawler to 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; execute on (Micro changes could be done by changing attributes via JMX 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; -- though again, you can&#39;t get at attributes in overrides).
